This paper discusses the vulnerability of datasets containing personal information to privacy breaches, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the methods used to de-anonymize such datasets, which involves machine learning and data mining techniques, falling under the categories of databases (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the privacy implications of such de-anonymization methods, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
